results.name: Smallest prime factor of the n-th 5-smooth number.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(A188427(n)) = 5 for n > 1. - _David A. Corneth_, Feb 07 2020
mathematica: FactorInteger[#][[1, 1]] & /@ Select[Range[3000], Last @ Map[First, FactorInteger[#]] <= 5 &] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Feb 07 2020 *)
program: (MAGMA) [1] cat [Min(PrimeDivisors(k)): k in [2..1500]| PrimeDivisors(k) subset [2, 3, 5]]; // _Marius A. Burtea_, Feb 07 2020
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 18 2005
